folder: Church Street & White Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Church Street, west side, south from and including White Street, showing the Eighth Ave., Subway in process of construction. In the right background is the Woolworth Building.

September 9, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Church Street & White Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Church Street, east side, south from but not including White to and including Franklin Streets, as seen from the Sixth Ave., extension at Walker Street.

March 19, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Church Street & White Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
At the convergance of Church Street and the new Sixth Ave. Extension at White Street. Shown on the right, is the west side of Church Street, north to and including Canal Street. Prominently shown, is the N.Y. Telephone Building which fronts on Walker, Lispenard and Church Streets and the new Sixth Ave. Extension.

June 3, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Church Street & White Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
Church Street, east side, north from White to Walker Streets as viewed eastward from and across Sixth Ave. Extension. The white 3-story structure at the N.E. corner of White Street bears No. 34 on same. The large office building in the background is No. 401 Broadway,
at the N.W. corner of Walker Street.

May 2, 1938.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
Church Street, West side, looking North from White Street.

July 12th, 1939.

P.L. Sperr.
